&gt;It does not actually create a record in the database but clears Model::$id and sets Model::$data based on your database field defaults. If you have not defined defaults for your database fields, &lt;strong&gt;Model::$data will be set to an empty array.&lt;/strong&gt;


You need to move line `$this-&gt;ItemType-&gt;create();`  to just before your `save` Method.

Your code should be like below:

````
        $this-&gt;ItemType-&gt;set($this-&gt;request-&gt;data);
