Linq has a [`Zip`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.linq.enumerable.zip?redirectedfrom=MSDN&amp;view=netframework-4.8) method as well:

    var diff = a.Zip(b, (ai, bi) =&gt; ai - bi);

Note that one potential bug in your code is if `b` has fewer elements than `a` then you&#39;d get an exception when you try to access an element outside the range of `b`. `Zip` will only return items as long as _both_ collections have items, which is effectively the shorter of the two collection lengths.

